  "doc_id": "246",
  "text": "POXase activity was measured according to an improved procedure [CITATION_1] . Briefly, 1.0 g of fresh soil was added to 3 mL of reagent solution (obtained by mixing 1.5 mL of catechol solution with 1.5 mL of proline solution) and 2 mL of phosphate buffer (0.1 M, pH 6.5). The suspension was swirled and incubated at 37uC for 1 h, then reaction was stopped by cooling and adding 5 mL of ethanol. The mixture was centrifuged at 4000 g at 4uC for 5 min. The absorbance of the supernatant fraction was determined at 525 nm. Assays without soil and catechol were carried out simultaneously as controls. POXase activity was expressed as mmol oxidized catechol (o-catechol) g",
